quran[26]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,77,"and made his offspring<sup>19</sup> the only survivors,","[19] i.e., Noah’s offspring: Shem, Ham, and Japheth."
  37,78,"and We left for him [a favorable mention] among later generations:",""
  37,79,"“Peace be upon Noah among all the nations.”",""
  37,80,"This is how We reward those who do good.",""
  37,81,"He was one of Our believing slaves.",""
  37,82,"Then we drowned the others.",""
  37,83,"Indeed, Abraham was one of those who followed his way.",""
  37,84,"When he came to his Lord with a sound heart,",""
  37,85,"and said to his father and his people, “What are you worshiping?",""
  37,86,"Is it false gods that you seek other than Allah?",""
  37,87,"Then what do you think of the Lord of the worlds?”",""
  37,88,"He then cast a glance at the stars<sup>20</sup>,","[20] His people had faith in astrology, so Abraham pretended to do the same to show them that he was not able to join them at their pagan feast and to remain in their temple of idols, while he was planning to destroy their idols."
  37,89,"and said, “I am sick<sup>21</sup>.”","[21] The Prophet (ﷺ) said: “Ibrahim (peace be upon him) did not lie except for three lies: His saying {I am sick} and his saying {Rather, the chief of them did this} and his saying about his wife, “She is my sister.” [Al-Bukhāri, Muslim]. Two of them were for the sake of Allah, and the third one was for the sake of his sister."
  37,90,"So they went away from him and left.",""
  37,91,"Then he turned to their gods and said, “Why do you not eat<sup>22</sup>?","[22] The offerings placed before you."
  37,92,"What is wrong with you that you do not speak?”",""
  37,93,"Then he turned upon them, striking them with his right hand.",""
  37,94,"Then his people came rushing towards him.",""
  37,95,"He said, “Do you worship what you yourselves carve,",""
  37,96,"when it is Allah Who created you and all what you do?”",""
  37,97,"They said, “Build a pyre for him and throw him into the blazing fire.”",""
  37,98,"They contrived a plan against him, but We made them the lowest.",""
  37,99,"He said, “I am going to my Lord; He will guide me.",""
  37,100,"My Lord, grant me righteous offspring.”",""
  37,101,"So We gave him glad tidings of a forbearing boy<sup>23</sup>.","[23] i.e., Ishmael"
  37,102,"Then when he reached the age where he could work with him, Abraham said, “O my dear son, I have seen in a dream that I must sacrifice you. What do you think?” He said, “O my dear father, do as you are commanded. You will find me, if Allah wills, one of the steadfast.”",""
